<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <%- include('partials/head') %> 
<body>
    <div class="glow-bg"></div>

    <%- include('partials/nav') %> 

    <div class="container">
        <header>
            <div class="logo-title">WLite Engine</div>
            <div class="subtitle">Quick setup guide, environment configuration, and local initialization steps for the core ecosystem.</div>
        </header>

        <!-- Step 1: Clone & Deps -->
        <section class="card">
            <h2>
                <span>⚡</span> Step 1: Cloning & Dependencies
            </h2>
            <p>First, clone the repository to your local machine and install all required packages:</p>
            
            <div class="code-block">
<span class="code-comment"># Clone the repository locally</span>
git clone https://github.com/david9sargsian9s/Wlite.git

<span class="code-comment"># Navigate to the project directory</span>
cd Wlite

<span class="code-comment"># Install all node dependencies</span>
npm install</div>
        </section>

        <!-- Step 2: Env Configuration -->
        <section class="card">
            <h2>
                <span>⚙️</span> Step 2: Environment Configuration (.env)
            </h2>
            <p>Create a file named <strong>.env</strong> in the root directory of your project and populate it with your specific API keys, database credentials, and OAuth tokens:</p>
            
            <div class="env-grid">
                <div class="env-line"><span>ATLAS_URL</span>=mongodb+srv://... <span class="code-comment"># Connection string to your MongoDB cluster</span></div>
                <div class="env-line"><span>PORT</span>=... <span class="code-comment"># Local port for the application</span></div>
                <div class="env-line"><span>JWT_ACCESS_SECRET</span>=... <span class="code-comment"># Secret for access token generation</span></div>
                <div class="env-line"><span>JWT_REFRESH_SECRET</span>=... <span class="code-comment"># Secret for refresh token generation</span></div>
                
                <div class="code-comment" style="margin: 5px 0;"># Google OAuth</div>
                <div class="env-line"><span>GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID</span>=...</div>
                <div class="env-line"><span>GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET</span>=...</div>
                
                <div class="code-comment" style="margin: 5px 0;"># Github OAuth</div>
                <div class="env-line"><span>GITHUB_CLIENT_ID</span>=...</div>
                <div class="env-line"><span>GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET</span>=...</div>
                
                <div class="code-comment" style="margin: 5px 0;"># My technical google account</div>
                <div class="env-line"><span>TECHNICAL_ACCOUNT</span>=...</div>
                <div class="env-line"><span>TECHNICAL_ACCOUNT_PASS</span>=...</div>
                
                <div class="code-comment" style="margin: 5px 0;"># Session secret</div>
                <div class="env-line"><span>SESSION_SECRET</span>=...</div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Step 3: Initialization -->
        <section class="card">
            <h2>
                <span>🚀</span> Step 3: Initialization Methods
            </h2>
            <p>Pick the run method that matches your environment goals:</p>

            <div class="grid-methods">
                <!-- Standard Build -->
                <div class="method-box production">
                    <span class="badge badge-cyan">Recommended</span>
                    <h3>Standard Build</h3>
                    <p>Best for stable execution of the local engine. Compiles TypeScript directly to production-ready JS.</p>
                    <div class="code-block" style="font-size: 0.85rem;">
npm run build
npm start</div>
                </div>

                <!-- Dev Mode -->
                <div class="method-box dev">
                    <span class="badge badge-red">Developers Only</span>
                    <h3>Development Mode</h3>
                    <p>Launches the project with nodemon enabled for hot-reloading when source files are modified.</p>
                    <div class="code-block" style="font-size: 0.85rem;">
npm run dev</div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Warning Notice -->
            <div class="warning-note">
                <strong>Notice for Developers:</strong> The project is actively developing; therefore, you might encounter unexpected issues in development mode. To avoid errors, using the standard production build is highly recommended.
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>